<ul class="task-constraints">
<li><b>Time limit:</b> 1.00 s</li>
<li><b>Memory limit:</b> 512 MB</li>
</ul>
<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="1741">
Given $n$ rectangles, your task is to determine the total area of their union.<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The first input line has an integer $n$: the number of rectangles.<br />
<br />
After that, there are $n$ lines describing the rectangles. Each line has four integers $x_1$, $y_1$, $x_2$ and $y_2$: a rectangle begins at point $(x_1,y_1)$ and ends at point $(x_2,y_2)$.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print the total area covered by the rectangles.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le n \le 10^5$<br />
<li>$-10^6 \le x_1 &lt; x_2 \le 10^6$<br />
<li>$-10^6 \le y_1 &lt; y_2 \le 10^6$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>3<br />
1 3 4 5<br />
3 1 7 4<br />
5 3 8 6</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>24</code>    </div>
